==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poncho
<hw>Pon"cho</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Ponchos</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Sp.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A kind of cloak worn by the Spanish Americans, having the form of a
blanket, with a slit in the middle for the head to pass through. A kind
of <xex>poncho</xex> made of rubber or painted cloth is used by the
mounted troops in the United States service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A trade name for camlets, or stout
worsteds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pond</ent>⟦br⟧
